# My Daughter - A Memoir of Family, Cancer and Transition

## By: Pim Bax

What do you do when your mother tells you she is dying? In what language do you share the news with your father? How do you explain it to your children?

Pim Bax wrote this remarkable memoir between the diagnosis of cancer in her mother and her death. At the core of this beautiful story is her relationship with her mother, which turns out to be a bond much richer than she realises.

The book switches from past to present, from Pim to her mother Beatrice, providing a unique view of their relationship, where Pim seeks to unravel the reasons for her mother’s lack of intimacy. In the end, it is her mother Beatrice who gives Pim all the answers, but only if Pim is prepared to open up and embrace herself.

The Media in Regional Development (MRD) project was established in October 1999 in the Department of Media and Communication, Norwegian University of Science and Technology (NTNU). The overall purpose of the research project is to contribute new knowledge that can help to understand how the media contribute to regional development.

The project focuses in particular on the following issues:

1. Doing better research: how to better conceptualise, understand, and measure the media’s contribution to regional development.

2. The contribution of online media to regional development (especially for e-commerce and online community development).
